blocking issue 2 is already fixed.\n\n3. **ConfirmationDialog tests** - Still ne
ed fixing. The tests "should call onConfirm callback" and "should call onCancel 
callback" only call `show()` and check `visible`. They need to actually trigger 
the button clicks.\n\n4. **ConfirmationDialog.show(config)** - The `title` and `
message` updates are commented out/empty. Need to either implement them or docum
ent the limitation.\n\nSince the user asked me to fix according to the review re
port, and issues 1 & 2 seem already fixed in commit 8acc236, I should focus on:\
n- Fixing `ConfirmationDialog` tests (issue 3)\n- Fixing `ConfirmationDialog.sho
w(config)` to handle title/message updates or document it (issue 4)\n- Optionall
y fixing `TopInfoBar.setAvatar()` fallback (non-blocking suggestion)\n\nWait, le
t me re-examine the current ConfirmationDialog code more carefully. It extends U
IDialog and stores `confirmCallback` and `cancelCallback`, but when `show(config
)` is called, it only updates those callbacks, not the title/message. Also, the 
original constructor passes `onConfirm` and `onCancel` directly to UIDialog. But
then `show()` overrides them with `confirmCallback`/`cancelCallback`. \n\nActual
ly, looking at UIDialog, `config.onConfirm` is called in `confirm()`. But Confir
mationDialog doesn\'t override `confirm()` to use its own callbacks. So when but
tons are clicked, UIDialog\'s `config.onConfirm` is used, not `confirmCallback`.
This means updating `confirmCallback` in `show()` has no effect!\n\nWait, let me
trace through:\n- Constructor: passes `config.onConfirm` to UIDialog constructor
→ stored in `this.config.onConfirm`\n- `show(config)`: updates `this.confirmCall
back` but NOT `this.config.onConfirm` in UIDialog\n- When confirm button clicked
: `UIButton.onClick` → `this.confirm()` → `this.config.onConfirm()` (UIDialog\'s
config)\n\nSo the callback update in `show()` is actually broken! It doesn\'t wo
rk because UIDialog uses its own internal config.\n\nLet me look at how to fix t
his properly. ConfirmationDialog should override `confirm()` and `cancel()` to u
se its own callbacks, or it should update UIDialog\'s config.\n\nActually, the s
